WEBVTT

00:00.258 --> 00:01.914
<i>Previously on "Midnight, Texas"...</i>

00:01.948 --> 00:03.315
<i>You can't run from me.</i>

00:03.343 --> 00:04.820
<i>I need to disappear.</i>

00:04.851 --> 00:06.741
You'll be safe in Midnight.

00:06.776 --> 00:08.743
<i>Aubrey wasn't who you saw.</i>

00:08.778 --> 00:10.412
<i>She was married five years ago.</i>

00:10.446 --> 00:11.713
<i>The name's Peter Lowry.</i>

00:11.747 --> 00:13.048
<i>So, a white supremacist?</i>

00:13.082 --> 00:15.583
Tell Lowry to stop coming after me.

00:15.618 --> 00:17.452
[Grunts]

00:17.486 --> 00:19.521
- You're my best friend.
- Is that it?

00:19.555 --> 00:21.523
If you want this thing
between us to continue,

00:21.557 --> 00:22.924
it means my dad can not know

00:22.958 --> 00:24.418
what we've been doing
on my lunch breaks.

00:24.420 --> 00:26.393
I need you to hear
Hightower's latest message.

00:26.395 --> 00:27.831
<i>It'll be the last thing you hear.</i>

00:27.862 --> 00:29.564
He wants my heart on a platter.

00:31.440 --> 00:34.102
<i>[Subtle Dark Music]</i>

00:34.136 --> 00:38.807
<i>♪</i>

00:38.841 --> 00:40.809
[Loud Thump]

00:40.843 --> 00:47.916
<i>♪</i>

00:55.691 --> 01:02.764
<i>♪</i>

01:04.934 --> 01:07.702
[Playing Light Melody]

01:09.105 --> 01:12.073
♪

01:12.108 --> 01:15.076
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

01:15.111 --> 01:22.217
<i>♪</i>

01:28.657 --> 01:30.625
[Wind Whistling]

01:30.659 --> 01:32.347
He knows where I live.

01:32.378 --> 01:35.062
Would've been easy enough to
shoot me when I opened the door,

01:35.064 --> 01:36.531
but he didn't.

01:36.565 --> 01:38.700
He wants to make you suffer first.

01:38.734 --> 01:41.136
Yeah, he's doing a pretty good job.

01:41.170 --> 01:44.873
Hon, I wish I never
got you into this mess.

01:44.907 --> 01:46.875
Didn't even have the
decency to stay alive

01:46.909 --> 01:48.009
to help me out of it.

01:48.043 --> 01:49.544
[Chuckles Lightly]

01:49.578 --> 01:53.615
Truth is, I wanted that
money as much as you.

01:53.649 --> 01:54.782
Do I meet him?

01:54.817 --> 01:56.784
No.

01:56.819 --> 01:59.087
You ask for help.

02:01.724 --> 02:04.692
<i>[Sultry Music]</i>

02:04.727 --> 02:05.960
<i>♪</i>

02:05.995 --> 02:09.163
[Cat Yowls, Hisses]

02:09.198 --> 02:11.733
Stop that, Mr. Snuggly.
My goddess, you're rude.

02:11.767 --> 02:14.502
He'll warm to me.

02:14.537 --> 02:17.238
Everyone does, eventually.

02:17.273 --> 02:19.240
Eventually.

02:19.275 --> 02:22.510
You... are you, um, hungry?

02:22.545 --> 02:24.012
I can make us pancakes.

02:24.046 --> 02:25.880
Yeah, I'll have some.

02:25.915 --> 02:27.515
[Engines Revving Outside]

02:27.550 --> 02:29.017
Stay here.

02:29.051 --> 02:32.153
[Engines Rumbling]

02:33.122 --> 02:36.090
<i>[Rock Music]</i>

02:36.125 --> 02:43.198
<i>♪</i>

02:45.000 --> 02:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:54.910 --> 02:57.011
- It's a fire.
- What's going on?

02:57.046 --> 02:59.948
Some water. Get some water.

02:59.982 --> 03:02.684
Lem and Olivia are still in there.

03:02.718 --> 03:03.685
Come on.

03:03.719 --> 03:04.852
- What?
- Oh!

03:04.887 --> 03:07.855
<i>[Suspenseful Music]</i>

03:07.890 --> 03:10.058
<i>♪</i>

03:10.092 --> 03:12.860
[Grunts]

03:12.895 --> 03:15.897
No, no, no, no, stay back, stay back.

03:15.931 --> 03:18.900
[Indistinct Chatter]

03:18.934 --> 03:23.037
<i>♪</i>

03:27.910 --> 03:29.944
The Sons of Lucifer did this?

03:31.280 --> 03:33.948
[Coughs] Olivia!

03:33.983 --> 03:36.251
[Coughing]

03:36.285 --> 03:37.619
Lem okay?

03:37.653 --> 03:38.886
Yeah, he slept through it.

03:38.921 --> 03:40.888
He doesn't have to breathe. I do.

03:40.923 --> 03:42.417
- [Both Coughing]
- I'll be right out.

03:42.448 --> 03:45.226
Just a big ol' distraction.

03:45.261 --> 03:48.730
- Who's there?
- Down here, dimwit.

03:48.764 --> 03:50.331
- Fiji's cat?
- Yep,

03:50.366 --> 03:52.634
and oh, my beeswax, the cat talks.

03:52.668 --> 03:55.069
Now that that's out of
the way, we got to move on.

03:55.104 --> 03:56.738
They took Fiji.

03:56.772 --> 03:58.306
What do you mean they took her?

03:58.340 --> 04:01.609
I mean they came in the store,
put a thingy over her mouth,

04:01.644 --> 04:04.078
and dragged her out... She's gone.

04:04.113 --> 04:06.981
[Phone Rings]

04:07.016 --> 04:11.819
She feeds me. Can't
be away for too long.

04:11.854 --> 04:13.888
[Ringing]

04:16.692 --> 04:18.259
Bobo Winthrop.

04:18.293 --> 04:21.262
Well, this has been a long time coming.

04:21.297 --> 04:23.031
I suspect you know who I am.

04:23.065 --> 04:25.700
Peter Lowry.

04:25.734 --> 04:27.168
So, Winthrop, is there anything

04:27.202 --> 04:30.838
you'd like to say to me?

04:30.873 --> 04:33.675
Where's Fiji?

04:33.709 --> 04:37.111
I'm disappointed. I was
expecting an apology.

04:37.146 --> 04:38.813
You know, "Sorry about Aubrey"?

04:38.847 --> 04:40.815
What?

04:40.849 --> 04:42.817
What did you do with Fiji?

04:42.851 --> 04:45.219
She's fine for now.

04:45.254 --> 04:47.789
She'll be fine as long
as I get what I want.

04:47.823 --> 04:49.347
I want the weapons. I want the money.

04:49.350 --> 04:50.707
I want all of it.

04:50.726 --> 04:52.994
Done. Where do you want to meet?

04:53.028 --> 04:54.553
I'll get back to you.

04:54.592 --> 04:57.318
No, wait, let's do this
now. I can be ready...

04:57.366 --> 05:00.001
[Dial Tone Drones]

05:01.937 --> 05:04.906
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

05:04.940 --> 05:12.013
<i>♪</i>

05:17.920 --> 05:19.153
Let's go.

05:19.188 --> 05:22.423
<i>♪</i>

05:22.740 --> 05:27.428
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

05:27.463 --> 05:30.431
<i>[Upbeat Folk Music]</i>

05:30.466 --> 05:37.739
<i>♪</i>

05:38.474 --> 05:41.042
- Hi.
- Hey.

05:41.076 --> 05:42.844
It's a slow morning.
Apparently pipe bombs

05:42.878 --> 05:44.746
drive off customers.

05:44.780 --> 05:47.348
- Makes sense.
- Mm-hmm.

05:47.383 --> 05:50.051
You ever think about leaving Midnight?

05:50.085 --> 05:52.387
All the time.

05:52.421 --> 05:54.922
Well, um, what if we did?

05:54.957 --> 05:58.092
Vegas, Grand Canyon. I've
got a house with wheels.

05:58.127 --> 06:00.194
It's doable.

06:00.229 --> 06:01.863
Why are you running?

06:01.897 --> 06:03.865
I'm not running.

06:03.899 --> 06:05.900
[Both Chuckle Lightly]

06:05.934 --> 06:08.870
It's this guy I owe money to.

06:08.904 --> 06:10.471
The one who shot you?

06:10.506 --> 06:13.875
Yeah, he sort of found
me, and I thought...

06:13.909 --> 06:16.978
That he wouldn't find
you in the Grand Canyon?

06:17.012 --> 06:19.046
Yeah. That.

06:19.081 --> 06:22.116
I'm not leaving my brother
here alone with my dad.

06:22.151 --> 06:24.752
You know that.

06:24.787 --> 06:28.756
Can't blame a guy for trying.

06:28.791 --> 06:30.758
You don't have to run, you know?

06:30.793 --> 06:32.393
You could ask people for help.

06:32.428 --> 06:33.895
The timing's not great,

06:33.929 --> 06:35.930
what with Bobo's being bombed and all.

06:35.964 --> 06:38.132
That doesn't mean that folks won't help.

06:38.167 --> 06:41.402
- [Sighs]
- Unless you want to run.

06:41.437 --> 06:43.771
Well, yeah, it's my instinct to bolt.

06:43.806 --> 06:46.107
It's what I do. It's
what I've always done.

06:46.125 --> 06:48.427
<i>[Solemn Music]</i>

06:48.477 --> 06:53.080
Except that maybe for
the first time ever

06:53.115 --> 06:57.084
I feel like I've got
a reason to stay put.

06:57.119 --> 06:59.287
<i>♪</i>

06:59.321 --> 07:02.790
So, Creek, do I?

07:04.526 --> 07:07.495
You do. You stay put.

07:07.529 --> 07:10.031
Okay, good. Great.

07:10.065 --> 07:11.499
[Laughs Softly]

07:11.533 --> 07:14.502
Um, can I borrow your car?

07:14.536 --> 07:18.272
<i>[Tense Music]</i>

07:18.307 --> 07:20.775
Bobo?

07:20.809 --> 07:24.145
You here?

07:24.179 --> 07:26.113
These have been in my
family for a long time.

07:26.148 --> 07:28.149
Some of it dates back
to the 13th century.

07:28.183 --> 07:30.151
How much you want for all this?

07:30.185 --> 07:32.019
Um, 20,000.

07:32.054 --> 07:33.888
15.

07:33.922 --> 07:38.159
<i>♪</i>

07:38.193 --> 07:40.061
I really appreciate it.

07:40.095 --> 07:43.231
You want a pistol?

07:43.265 --> 07:44.799
What makes you think...

07:44.833 --> 07:47.835
Oh, I don't know.

07:47.870 --> 07:49.303
Maybe.

07:49.338 --> 07:52.306
Might not be bad to have.

07:52.341 --> 07:55.977
<i>♪</i>

07:56.011 --> 07:59.146
Sorry about what happened.

07:59.181 --> 08:01.482
At least no one got hurt.

08:01.517 --> 08:05.987
<i>♪</i>

08:06.021 --> 08:08.356
[Inhales Deeply]

08:11.260 --> 08:17.265
<i>♪</i>

08:17.299 --> 08:18.933
Hello?

08:18.967 --> 08:21.168
<i>Somebody. Please.</i>

08:21.203 --> 08:22.603
Aw.

08:22.638 --> 08:24.939
<i>Hey, there, Curly.</i>

08:24.973 --> 08:28.276
<i>I thought you were gonna sleep all day.</i>

08:28.310 --> 08:30.845
[Weakly] You don't...

08:30.879 --> 08:34.181
<i>you don't know what I'm... capable...</i>

08:34.216 --> 08:35.414
Well, right now, you're not capable

08:35.417 --> 08:36.583
of finishing that thought.

08:36.618 --> 08:38.119
And I do know.

08:38.153 --> 08:39.554
Heard all about your little trick

08:39.587 --> 08:41.522
with the pool cue down
at the Cartoon Saloon.

08:41.557 --> 08:43.256
Very impressive.

08:43.292 --> 08:46.227
<i>The drowsiness? That's
the fentanyl patch.</i>

08:46.261 --> 08:50.431
It's like morphine, but
a hundred times stronger.

08:50.465 --> 08:53.034
It'll keep you from doing
that voodoo that you do.

08:53.068 --> 08:56.871
You won't stop... Stop me.

08:56.913 --> 08:59.882
Okay, just keep telling yourself that.

08:59.908 --> 09:00.975
<i>♪</i>

09:01.009 --> 09:03.144
[Groans]

09:03.178 --> 09:06.414
You... you won't...

09:06.448 --> 09:08.416
you...

09:13.655 --> 09:16.624
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

09:16.658 --> 09:23.931
<i>♪</i>

09:31.624 --> 09:35.110
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

09:35.145 --> 09:37.146
<i>♪</i>

09:37.180 --> 09:39.748
Who did this?

09:39.783 --> 09:41.951
Sons of Lucifer.

09:41.985 --> 09:45.287
It's me they're after,
so let me take care of it.

09:45.322 --> 09:47.189
It stopped being just about you

09:47.224 --> 09:49.692
when they bombed Olivia's home.

09:49.726 --> 09:52.828
[Phone Ringing]

09:57.901 --> 09:59.702
Tell me where and when.

09:59.736 --> 10:01.303
<i>Service road off Ranchville Drive.</i>

10:01.338 --> 10:02.530
<i>Come alone.</i>

10:02.553 --> 10:04.273
<i>We see anyone else, Curly's dead.</i>

10:04.307 --> 10:06.141
<i>You understand me?</i>

10:06.176 --> 10:08.143
Yeah. I understand.

10:08.178 --> 10:09.612
[Line Clicks]

10:11.681 --> 10:14.316
I remember when you first moved here.

10:14.351 --> 10:18.053
Offered to buy this shop in cash.

10:18.088 --> 10:20.856
I knew you were running
from something bad.

10:20.890 --> 10:23.659
I didn't ask questions then.

10:23.693 --> 10:26.328
I'm asking now.

10:26.363 --> 10:28.230
What do they want from you?

10:28.265 --> 10:29.732
[Knocking At Door]

10:29.766 --> 10:32.735
<i>[Tense Music]</i>

10:32.769 --> 10:34.136
<i>♪</i>

10:34.170 --> 10:36.672
In case the bikers come back.

10:36.706 --> 10:38.874
<i>♪</i>

10:38.908 --> 10:40.743
Can I come in?

10:40.777 --> 10:43.045
I once asked you what
you did for a living,

10:43.079 --> 10:44.313
and you said...

10:44.347 --> 10:45.814
People got problems. They hire me

10:45.849 --> 10:47.383
to get rid of those problems.

10:47.417 --> 10:48.851
Right.

10:48.885 --> 10:51.720
Manfred has problems.

10:51.755 --> 10:53.322
Oh.

10:56.726 --> 11:03.832
<i>♪</i>

11:15.145 --> 11:16.912
You're right.

11:16.946 --> 11:21.250
I was running... from my family.

11:21.284 --> 11:23.018
This belonged to your family?

11:23.053 --> 11:28.624
Yeah, my parents are wealthy,
well-connected, and...

11:28.658 --> 11:30.292
white supremacists.

11:30.327 --> 11:33.295
<i>♪</i>

11:33.330 --> 11:35.164
Oh.

11:36.333 --> 11:42.304
<i>♪</i>

11:42.339 --> 11:45.741
Hightower?

11:45.775 --> 11:47.242
I'm here.

11:47.277 --> 11:49.378
I've got money.

11:50.347 --> 11:57.252
<i>♪</i>

11:57.287 --> 11:59.820
They had big plans for this stuff.

11:59.843 --> 12:01.990
Once I found out about it,

12:02.025 --> 12:03.926
I didn't want it on my conscience,

12:03.960 --> 12:05.294
so I left.

12:05.328 --> 12:07.396
With their stuff?

12:07.430 --> 12:09.431
Story spread.

12:09.466 --> 12:13.235
This cache became a holy grail of sorts

12:13.269 --> 12:15.938
for the white power crowd.

12:15.972 --> 12:18.407
One of Lowry's guys must
have figured out who I was.

12:18.441 --> 12:20.175
That's why he sent Aubrey.

12:20.210 --> 12:25.914
Manfred said that Aubrey's
feelings for me were real.

12:25.949 --> 12:29.351
That's probably why Lowry killed her.

12:29.386 --> 12:31.019
Now he's got Fiji.

12:31.054 --> 12:33.355
Not for long. Let's bring her home.

12:33.390 --> 12:35.958
Lem, I got to go alone.

12:35.992 --> 12:39.194
If I don't, they'll kill her.

12:39.229 --> 12:41.196
I can't take that risk.

12:41.231 --> 12:43.432
I'm afraid that doesn't work for me.

12:43.466 --> 12:50.773
<i>♪</i>

12:55.845 --> 12:57.212
[Footstep Crunches]

12:57.247 --> 12:58.447
[Gun Clicks]

12:58.481 --> 13:00.449
Safety's on.

13:00.483 --> 13:03.385
Why are you here, and how'd you find me?

13:03.420 --> 13:05.354
Creek asked me, and I found the note

13:05.388 --> 13:07.489
in the Manfred-in-the-box.

13:07.524 --> 13:09.992
[Sighs] I appreciate the concern.

13:10.026 --> 13:11.894
Don't appreciate you
breaking into my RV.

13:11.928 --> 13:13.162
Either way, I got this.

13:13.196 --> 13:15.164
Do you?

13:15.198 --> 13:17.299
Look, I'm a professional.

13:17.333 --> 13:20.035
You rescued Lem from the
vampire nest, so I owe you,

13:20.069 --> 13:23.005
and I don't like owing people.

13:23.039 --> 13:25.174
I don't want you to get hurt.

13:25.208 --> 13:26.909
I won't.

13:26.943 --> 13:28.907
So, this guy...

13:28.927 --> 13:30.494
Your grandma conned him?

13:30.524 --> 13:32.381
Out of $100,000.

13:32.415 --> 13:34.316
I got 78 with me.

13:34.350 --> 13:36.318
I'll front you the rest.

13:36.352 --> 13:41.390
<i>♪</i>

13:41.424 --> 13:44.493
Let's get this weirdo.

13:44.527 --> 13:51.834
<i>♪</i>

14:00.243 --> 14:02.044
It's okay.

14:02.078 --> 14:04.279
I got cash. I'm ready to settle this.

14:04.314 --> 14:05.914
Added bonus:

14:05.949 --> 14:09.384
you settle, and I
don't have to kill you.

14:09.419 --> 14:11.386
<i>♪</i>

14:11.421 --> 14:12.921
Too late.

14:12.956 --> 14:14.289
What are you talking about?

14:14.324 --> 14:15.891
<i>♪</i>

14:15.925 --> 14:17.559
Oh, jeez.

14:17.594 --> 14:19.228
Violet.

14:19.262 --> 14:22.865
Not... Hightower?

14:22.899 --> 14:24.867
No.

14:24.901 --> 14:26.101
That's his daughter.

14:26.135 --> 14:28.937
What else is she?

14:28.972 --> 14:33.108
Manfred, just tell her.

14:33.142 --> 14:35.683
<i>♪</i>

14:35.710 --> 14:38.012
Violet was...

14:38.042 --> 14:40.449
[Sighs] She and I were engaged.

14:40.483 --> 14:44.712
You walked out on her,
left her at the altar.

14:44.736 --> 14:47.890
Well, that's not very nice.

14:47.924 --> 14:50.559
And it's also not why I'm here.

14:50.593 --> 14:54.263
$100,000. I'll throw in interest.

14:54.297 --> 14:56.164
That work for you?

14:56.199 --> 14:59.935
No... not really.

14:59.969 --> 15:02.471
<i>♪</i>

15:02.505 --> 15:05.574
[Gunshots]

15:08.511 --> 15:11.013
Might've mentioned the
whole telekinetic thing!

15:11.047 --> 15:12.848
That's black magic. It's bad.

15:12.882 --> 15:14.182
Yeah, I see that!

15:14.217 --> 15:15.517
[Guns Clicking]

15:15.552 --> 15:16.618
[Guns Clatter]

15:16.653 --> 15:18.587
- Let's get out.
- Yeah.

15:19.522 --> 15:22.591
Manfred!

15:24.875 --> 15:27.109
You can't outrun me!

15:30.017 --> 15:33.624
<i>[Tense Music]</i>

15:33.658 --> 15:39.630
<i>♪</i>

15:41.533 --> 15:43.300
Is everything settled?

15:43.335 --> 15:45.803
Oh, we're not even in
the vicinity of settled.

15:45.837 --> 15:47.338
What's going on?

15:47.372 --> 15:50.074
[Exhales Sharply] Yeah, Manfred,

15:50.108 --> 15:51.975
what's going on?

15:53.678 --> 15:56.814
It wasn't just my grandma who stole.

15:56.848 --> 15:58.415
Xylda and I did it together.

15:58.450 --> 16:01.518
We ran a grift on him.

16:01.553 --> 16:03.687
Okay, so you stole money.

16:03.722 --> 16:05.823
More than that.

16:05.857 --> 16:07.758
It's personal.

16:07.792 --> 16:10.694
Psychics, mediums run in my family.

16:10.729 --> 16:13.630
A power passed on by blood.

16:13.665 --> 16:16.651
Hightower's a gypsy, but no abilities.

16:16.674 --> 16:19.503
Except for that glass trick
that almost shredded us.

16:19.537 --> 16:21.972
He gave an eye for that.

16:22.006 --> 16:23.540
Hightower's old world,

16:23.575 --> 16:26.110
wanted to be patriarch
of a powerful family,

16:26.144 --> 16:27.644
a magical family.

16:27.679 --> 16:30.647
Where is this going?

16:30.682 --> 16:33.350
Xylda made him an offer.

16:33.385 --> 16:35.119
I'd marry his daughter, Violet.

16:35.153 --> 16:38.021
And get magic in his bloodline.

16:38.056 --> 16:40.078
Wow. So, Violet is...

16:40.109 --> 16:41.625
Dead.

16:41.659 --> 16:44.862
Dad's carting her corpse around.

16:44.896 --> 16:47.865
- Did you...
- No, no, no, I didn't kill her.

16:47.899 --> 16:49.967
<i>♪</i>

16:50.001 --> 16:52.836
I left her at the altar.

16:52.871 --> 16:55.706
Hightower paid Xylda
right before the ceremony.

16:55.740 --> 16:59.076
We took off as soon as
the wedding march started.

16:59.110 --> 17:01.078
<i>♪</i>

17:01.112 --> 17:03.747
A few weeks later, she killed herself.

17:03.782 --> 17:05.715
<i>♪</i>

17:05.750 --> 17:08.551
It's the worst thing I've ever done.

17:08.586 --> 17:10.854
I wish I could take it back.

17:12.190 --> 17:14.458
My break's almost over. I've got to go.

17:15.894 --> 17:18.862
<i>[Solemn Music]</i>

17:18.896 --> 17:21.832
<i>♪</i>

17:21.866 --> 17:23.500
I should've told you.

17:23.535 --> 17:25.435
No, I-I understand why you didn't,

17:25.470 --> 17:27.604
because it's awful, but the thing is

17:27.638 --> 17:29.907
that my dad has been telling
me that you're bad news

17:29.941 --> 17:31.575
and nothing but trouble

17:31.609 --> 17:36.079
and why did you have to
go and prove him right?

17:36.114 --> 17:40.217
<i>♪</i>

17:42.053 --> 17:45.022
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

17:45.056 --> 17:52.162
<i>♪</i>

18:06.644 --> 18:10.781
Remember me? From the cell.

18:10.815 --> 18:14.117
I got everything Lowry asked for.

18:14.152 --> 18:21.258
<i>♪</i>

18:24.095 --> 18:25.829
It's all there.

18:25.864 --> 18:32.169
<i>♪</i>

18:32.203 --> 18:34.538
We're good.

18:39.210 --> 18:41.144
Now where is she?

18:41.179 --> 18:43.280
Not here.

18:43.314 --> 18:45.115
We'll take you to her.

18:47.785 --> 18:49.486
After.

18:49.521 --> 18:52.656
<i>♪</i>

18:52.690 --> 18:54.124
[Grunts]

18:54.158 --> 18:56.026
Payback's a bitch.

18:56.060 --> 18:57.995
[Grunts]

18:58.029 --> 18:59.263
Get him!

18:59.297 --> 19:02.566
[Grunting, Pounding]

19:03.868 --> 19:07.204
<i>♪</i>

19:07.238 --> 19:09.573
[Grunting Continues]

19:11.009 --> 19:12.676
Lem, where the hell are you?

19:12.710 --> 19:14.845
Are you with Fiji? Bobo?

19:14.879 --> 19:16.813
Call me back.

19:18.683 --> 19:20.050
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

19:20.084 --> 19:22.886
Where is he, hm?

19:22.921 --> 19:24.187
Check his house?

19:24.222 --> 19:26.023
Of course I checked his house, his RV.

19:26.057 --> 19:27.624
Then I don't know what to tell you.

19:27.659 --> 19:29.155
Well, if you don't know what to tell me,

19:29.157 --> 19:30.327
would you know if...

19:30.361 --> 19:32.775
[Indistinct Chatter]

19:32.790 --> 19:34.197
<i>♪</i>

19:34.232 --> 19:36.567
If I flicked my finger

19:36.601 --> 19:39.803
and pushed that fork down her throat...

19:39.837 --> 19:42.873
Enough.

19:42.907 --> 19:45.008
I know where he's hiding.

19:47.946 --> 19:50.324
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

19:50.347 --> 19:52.249
<i>♪</i>

19:52.283 --> 19:55.018
Are you sure you want to do this?

19:55.053 --> 19:57.020
After you.

19:57.055 --> 20:04.127
<i>♪</i>

20:12.370 --> 20:14.037
Oh!

20:14.072 --> 20:15.372
<i>[Suspenseful Music]</i>

20:15.406 --> 20:17.908
- [Groaning]
- [Chains Rattling]

20:17.942 --> 20:23.013
<i>♪</i>

20:23.047 --> 20:25.182
No!

20:25.216 --> 20:27.851
No! No!

20:27.885 --> 20:29.286
Once you calm down, we'll talk.

20:29.320 --> 20:32.289
[Screaming]

20:32.323 --> 20:34.669
<i>♪</i>

20:37.360 --> 20:41.226
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

20:41.260 --> 20:48.366
<i>♪</i>

21:02.682 --> 21:04.416
- Hey.
- [Groans]

21:04.450 --> 21:08.286
[Gasping]

21:08.321 --> 21:10.388
Thought you'd be taller.

21:10.423 --> 21:14.326
I did everything you
asked. Where is she?

21:14.360 --> 21:15.760
She's alive...

21:15.795 --> 21:18.730
which is more than I
can say for my wife.

21:18.764 --> 21:23.268
What happened to
Aubrey... That's on you.

21:25.137 --> 21:27.105
I suppose in a way you're right.

21:27.139 --> 21:29.140
Wish I never involved her.

21:29.175 --> 21:30.742
Aubrey was so sweet. I figured she'd

21:30.776 --> 21:32.676
wrap you around her finger,
get the information out of you.

21:32.678 --> 21:34.779
I was wrong.

21:34.814 --> 21:38.316
I got what I want, but I don't have her.

21:38.351 --> 21:40.752
<i>♪</i>

21:40.786 --> 21:43.622
Anyway, let's find out what you brought.

21:43.656 --> 21:47.359
But if you hold out on
me, you try anything,

21:47.393 --> 21:50.362
I'll bury Fiji alive,
suffocate her slow.

21:50.396 --> 21:53.465
[Indistinct Chatter]

21:55.534 --> 21:59.504
<i>♪</i>

21:59.538 --> 22:01.606
He's settling down. I'm going in there.

22:01.641 --> 22:03.641
You know, it would be easier
and less of a time-suck

22:03.643 --> 22:04.876
if you'd just let me end it.

22:04.911 --> 22:06.611
Xylda and I were wrong
to do what we did,

22:06.646 --> 22:09.281
and Violet died because of it.

22:09.315 --> 22:13.652
I've been running from
this for a long time.

22:13.686 --> 22:17.656
It's finally caught up with
me. I need to man up, face it.

22:17.690 --> 22:19.224
[Sighs]

22:19.258 --> 22:21.897
This is about Creek, isn't it?

22:21.920 --> 22:23.527
I just want to get out from under this

22:23.529 --> 22:26.197
without more bloodshed.

22:26.232 --> 22:28.533
And yeah, it's about Creek.

22:28.567 --> 22:29.834
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

22:29.869 --> 22:32.537
But, um, since Hightower
was insane enough

22:32.571 --> 22:33.872
to sacrifice an eye for...

22:33.906 --> 22:35.907
I'll stand by.

22:35.942 --> 22:37.909
Yeah.

22:37.944 --> 22:45.216
<i>♪</i>

22:46.686 --> 22:48.353
You happy?

22:48.387 --> 22:51.823
Chaining me up like a dog?

22:51.857 --> 22:54.592
I'm not happy

22:54.627 --> 22:56.861
about any of this.

22:56.896 --> 22:58.430
I'll be happy when I'm not

22:58.464 --> 22:59.730
looking over my shoulder every day.

22:59.732 --> 23:02.334
[Footsteps Approaching]

23:02.368 --> 23:04.669
I saw you guys come up here.

23:04.704 --> 23:06.738
Manfred's with Hightower.

23:06.772 --> 23:09.341
Oh. Um, well...

23:09.375 --> 23:11.676
he's good at talking his
way out of things, so...

23:11.711 --> 23:13.445
He is. Right now

23:13.479 --> 23:16.781
he's trying to level with him, though.

23:16.816 --> 23:19.784
Mind if I stay?

23:19.819 --> 23:23.855
<i>♪</i>

23:23.889 --> 23:27.525
I can't defend what Xylda and I did.

23:27.560 --> 23:29.361
- I can't.
- No, you can't.

23:29.395 --> 23:31.262
I can tell you I'm not the same man.

23:31.297 --> 23:32.864
I've changed.

23:32.898 --> 23:35.633
And I'm willing to do
anything to settle this.

23:35.667 --> 23:39.403
Oh, you want to settle this, yeah?

23:39.438 --> 23:42.974
Well, let's see. What
is it that you owe?

23:43.009 --> 23:45.877
Well, there's the money you stole.

23:45.911 --> 23:49.447
There's the suffering.

23:49.482 --> 23:51.883
And finally there's her life.

23:51.917 --> 23:53.752
<i>♪</i>

23:53.786 --> 23:56.721
So, suffering?

23:56.756 --> 24:00.291
You want a life for a life?

24:00.326 --> 24:03.828
If that's what you want, we're even.

24:03.863 --> 24:06.598
Right after I bailed on the wedding,

24:06.632 --> 24:09.972
like, a day later, Xylda got sick.

24:10.011 --> 24:11.935
[Sighs] We went through the money fast.

24:11.937 --> 24:15.273
Chemo's pricey.

24:15.307 --> 24:18.743
While she was dying, we
joked that you finally got

24:18.778 --> 24:22.614
that power you always wanted, because...

24:22.648 --> 24:24.849
God, you cursed us hard.

24:24.884 --> 24:28.520
<i>♪</i>

24:28.554 --> 24:29.754
We both lost family.

24:29.789 --> 24:32.791
You lost nothing!

24:32.825 --> 24:35.693
You still see her.

24:35.728 --> 24:39.697
You still talk with her!

24:39.732 --> 24:41.933
You want to talk to Violet?

24:41.967 --> 24:43.601
No, no...

24:43.636 --> 24:44.936
I can make that happen.

24:44.970 --> 24:46.805
- No.
- Torturing me...

24:46.839 --> 24:47.806
What's it gotten you?

24:47.840 --> 24:49.808
You feel any better?

24:49.842 --> 24:51.443
Killing me won't bring her back.

24:51.477 --> 24:54.879
It won't give you closure.

24:54.914 --> 24:58.783
Maybe... maybe talking to Violet will.

24:58.818 --> 25:01.786
<i>[Rousing Music]</i>

25:01.821 --> 25:04.789
<i>♪</i>

25:04.824 --> 25:07.926
[Indistinct Chatter]

25:12.832 --> 25:15.366
Are we happy?

25:15.401 --> 25:17.836
We're real happy.

25:17.870 --> 25:19.471
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

25:19.505 --> 25:22.740
Looks like you held up
your end of the bargain,

25:22.775 --> 25:24.976
so I'll take you to her.

25:25.010 --> 25:28.046
[Indistinct Chatter]

25:29.949 --> 25:33.384
<i>♪</i>

25:33.419 --> 25:34.752
You moved her?

25:34.787 --> 25:37.856
I didn't want to leave
her out in the open.

25:39.859 --> 25:41.893
She's down there.

25:49.034 --> 25:51.536
[Grunts] What are you doing?

25:51.570 --> 25:54.339
Insurance policy. You do
what you said you'll do,

25:54.373 --> 25:56.877
give me peace, closure...

25:56.917 --> 25:57.884
[Bolts Lock]

25:57.916 --> 26:00.011
I'll let you leave.

26:00.045 --> 26:02.514
<i>♪</i>

26:02.548 --> 26:06.684
But if not...

26:06.719 --> 26:08.086
well, then,

26:08.120 --> 26:10.855
you'll join Violet.

26:10.890 --> 26:13.925
[Structure Rumbling]

26:18.364 --> 26:19.865
Fantastic.

26:28.047 --> 26:31.051
Hey, hey, hey.

26:31.085 --> 26:33.153
- [Groaning]
- Hey, look at me.

26:33.187 --> 26:35.555
Look at me.

26:35.590 --> 26:37.691
Are you okay?

26:37.725 --> 26:41.027
Hey, hey. Look at me, look at me.

26:41.062 --> 26:43.029
The patch. The patch.

26:43.064 --> 26:46.032
<i>[Solemn Music]</i>

26:46.067 --> 26:48.057
<i>♪</i>

26:48.073 --> 26:50.202
- If you hurt her...
- Are you kidding me, man?

26:50.204 --> 26:53.073
If I hurt her, what? My God!

26:53.107 --> 26:55.086
You killed my wife.

26:55.117 --> 26:56.076
I didn't!

26:56.110 --> 26:57.577
You've been lying so long

26:57.612 --> 26:59.146
you're starting to
believe them yourself.

26:59.148 --> 27:02.148
He doesn't lie.

27:02.183 --> 27:04.517
You don't know, do you?

27:04.552 --> 27:06.549
You don't know about his
family? About who he was

27:06.552 --> 27:08.588
before he came to your freak town?

27:08.623 --> 27:11.091
Mr. All-American here?

27:11.125 --> 27:12.692
He was once one of us.

27:12.727 --> 27:15.862
No, no, no. I'll explain later.

27:15.897 --> 27:17.497
[Laughing]

27:17.531 --> 27:19.900
You gonna explain that
church outside Atlanta?

27:19.934 --> 27:21.735
The one that got bombed?

27:21.769 --> 27:24.070
He was right there, ground zero.

27:24.105 --> 27:27.073
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

27:27.108 --> 27:31.711
<i>♪</i>

27:31.746 --> 27:34.614
Let us out of here.

27:34.649 --> 27:37.584
Uhh... no.

27:37.618 --> 27:40.887
You're gonna stay.

27:40.922 --> 27:43.023
And don't worry about the weapons.

27:43.057 --> 27:46.092
We'll be sure to make your daddy proud.

27:46.127 --> 27:47.794
[Breathing Heavily]

27:47.828 --> 27:50.931
Oh, yeah. [Laughing]

27:53.267 --> 27:55.001
[Gate Closes]

28:00.975 --> 28:03.476
Not bad.

28:03.511 --> 28:06.613
Now, how about a moving target? [Growls]

28:06.647 --> 28:08.615
[Distant Screams]

28:08.649 --> 28:10.050
[Distant Gunfire]

28:11.185 --> 28:13.486
What the hell are you waiting for?

28:13.521 --> 28:16.489
[Indistinct Chatter]

28:16.524 --> 28:19.159
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

28:19.193 --> 28:21.261
[Soaring, Then Explosion]

28:22.997 --> 28:25.065
Bet you that's Lem.

28:28.336 --> 28:29.903
What is it?

28:29.937 --> 28:32.172
Air's feeling a little, uh...

28:32.206 --> 28:33.306
Thin?

28:33.341 --> 28:35.742
[Explosion]

28:43.184 --> 28:46.252
[Grunting]

28:49.724 --> 28:52.692
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

28:52.727 --> 28:57.697
<i>♪</i>

28:57.732 --> 28:59.699
Violet...

28:59.734 --> 29:01.134
[Sighs]

29:01.168 --> 29:02.802
We didn't know each other all that well,

29:02.837 --> 29:05.538
but you seemed... nice.

29:05.573 --> 29:09.209
You... you can't be okay with this.

29:09.243 --> 29:11.778
I didn't do right by you, but...

29:11.812 --> 29:13.213
your father's insane,

29:13.247 --> 29:16.549
and I need help.

29:16.584 --> 29:19.552
[Wind Blows]

29:19.587 --> 29:21.554
[Eerie Whispers]

29:21.589 --> 29:23.289
<i>♪</i>

29:23.324 --> 29:25.625
God, Violet.

29:27.928 --> 29:30.163
I'm so sorry.

29:30.197 --> 29:32.298
I never meant to hurt you.

29:32.333 --> 29:34.167
You left.

29:34.201 --> 29:35.735
You didn't think that would hurt?

29:35.770 --> 29:37.837
Well, yeah, but I...

29:37.872 --> 29:40.340
I didn't think you'd
kill yourself over me.

29:40.374 --> 29:42.075
I didn't.

29:42.109 --> 29:44.577
<i>♪</i>

29:44.612 --> 29:47.080
So, where's my father?

29:47.114 --> 29:49.582
[Grunts]

29:49.617 --> 29:52.252
[Panting]

29:52.286 --> 29:54.888
Are you praying?

29:54.922 --> 29:58.158
Gathering all... the air we have.

30:00.694 --> 30:02.295
Come close.

30:08.135 --> 30:11.271
Again. Saving my life.

30:11.305 --> 30:14.074
We should save air.

30:14.108 --> 30:15.341
[Soaring And Explosion]

30:18.379 --> 30:20.680
Ashes to ashes.

30:22.249 --> 30:25.018
<i>[Rock Music]</i>

30:25.052 --> 30:27.020
How the hell is he still walking?

30:27.054 --> 30:29.022
Open fire!

30:29.056 --> 30:36.162
<i>♪</i>

30:45.973 --> 30:47.941
That hurt.

30:47.975 --> 30:49.742
[Screams]

30:51.178 --> 30:54.214
Violet's spirit is with me.

30:54.248 --> 30:57.884
How do I know you're telling the truth?

31:00.020 --> 31:02.122
Help me prove you're here.

31:04.692 --> 31:06.392
The night before you ran out on me,

31:06.427 --> 31:08.728
my dad have me a present.

31:10.364 --> 31:12.899
You gave her a christening dress

31:12.933 --> 31:14.434
for the grandchildren.

31:14.468 --> 31:16.669
You told her about her ancestors,

31:16.704 --> 31:19.530
how the Hightowers were
once powerful psychics.

31:19.561 --> 31:22.442
You thanked her for bringing
it back to the bloodline.

31:24.044 --> 31:26.179
Violet.

31:26.213 --> 31:28.281
[Voice Breaks] It's you.

31:28.315 --> 31:30.016
[Crying Softly]

31:30.050 --> 31:32.819
[Footsteps Descending]

31:34.889 --> 31:37.190
Now where is she?

31:37.224 --> 31:40.360
She's right here.

31:40.394 --> 31:43.329
Violet, what is it you want to tell him?

31:43.364 --> 31:45.298
You tell my daddy...

31:45.332 --> 31:47.800
I hope he rots in hell!

31:47.835 --> 31:50.436
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

31:59.124 --> 32:01.291
I'm sorry, Fiji.

32:02.927 --> 32:07.030
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Fiji.

32:08.165 --> 32:10.333
[Gasping]

32:10.368 --> 32:13.036
You okay? [Both Panting]

32:13.070 --> 32:14.838
- Are you?
- How about we talk

32:14.872 --> 32:16.639
once we're out of here?

32:17.675 --> 32:19.275
Come on.

32:21.078 --> 32:24.047
<i>[Tense Music]</i>

32:24.081 --> 32:30.019
<i>♪</i>

32:31.288 --> 32:32.355
Sun's almost up.

32:32.390 --> 32:34.224
I'll be quick.

32:34.258 --> 32:41.331
<i>♪</i>

32:44.101 --> 32:45.735
Oh!

32:45.770 --> 32:48.738
You took everything. My men, my wife...

32:48.773 --> 32:51.741
[Both Grunting]

32:51.776 --> 32:58.848
<i>♪</i>

33:03.287 --> 33:07.090
For the last time, I
did not kill Aubrey!

33:07.124 --> 33:10.226
[Both Shouting, Grunting]

33:12.296 --> 33:19.402
<i>♪</i>

33:20.771 --> 33:23.840
[Grunting Continues]

33:29.747 --> 33:36.853
<i>♪</i>

33:37.755 --> 33:40.857
[Gasping]

33:42.159 --> 33:46.963
<i>♪</i>

33:50.334 --> 33:52.402
Bobo.

33:54.271 --> 33:56.372
We should go.

33:59.143 --> 34:06.216
<i>♪</i>

34:10.120 --> 34:13.089
<i>[Rousing Music]</i>

34:13.123 --> 34:17.827
<i>♪</i>

34:17.862 --> 34:19.829
[Engine Turns Over]

34:27.505 --> 34:29.172
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

34:29.206 --> 34:33.275
What did she say? What
is my Violet telling you?

34:33.310 --> 34:36.145
Well, she's a little... upset.

34:36.179 --> 34:38.014
Of course she's upset. You left her!

34:38.047 --> 34:40.850
I agreed to marry
Manfred because of you!

34:40.885 --> 34:43.152
I wanted to please you!

34:43.187 --> 34:44.987
Uh, your opinion's important to her.

34:45.022 --> 34:47.857
Tell him the truth!

34:47.891 --> 34:52.228
The past, Violet... That's
another lifetime ago.

34:52.263 --> 34:55.864
We all did things we
wish we could take back.

34:55.900 --> 34:57.901
Your father held you back.

34:57.935 --> 34:59.335
He still does.

34:59.370 --> 35:01.037
You're still tethered to this world

35:01.071 --> 35:02.838
because you're not letting
go... You need to forgive...

35:02.840 --> 35:05.174
I'm done being told what to do!

35:05.209 --> 35:07.710
It's the only way you'll get closure,

35:07.745 --> 35:08.878
the only way he will.

35:08.913 --> 35:10.847
I can think of another way.

35:10.881 --> 35:12.849
[Gasps]

35:12.883 --> 35:15.852
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

35:15.886 --> 35:17.287
<i>♪</i>

35:18.522 --> 35:19.856
[Exhales]

35:19.890 --> 35:22.125
[Neck Cracks]

35:25.062 --> 35:26.529
Daddy.

35:26.564 --> 35:29.399
Violet?

35:29.433 --> 35:33.002
My entire life, you controlled me.

35:33.037 --> 35:35.171
<i>[Solemn Music]</i>

35:35.205 --> 35:40.009
Forced me to do what you wanted.

35:40.044 --> 35:43.413
Tried to marry me off like chattel.

35:43.447 --> 35:45.415
<i>♪</i>

35:45.449 --> 35:48.184
I never mattered.

35:48.218 --> 35:50.954
I was always a means to an end!

35:50.988 --> 35:52.288
No.

35:52.323 --> 35:53.856
No, I...

35:53.891 --> 35:55.458
I am...

35:55.492 --> 35:57.460
I am sorry.

35:57.494 --> 35:59.395
If I could do it again...

35:59.430 --> 36:01.397
You can't!

36:01.432 --> 36:04.033
But I can.

36:04.068 --> 36:07.036
I killed the wrong person that night.

36:07.071 --> 36:10.039
<i>[Dramatic Music]</i>

36:10.074 --> 36:15.912
<i>♪</i>

36:15.946 --> 36:18.781
Violet, enough!

36:18.816 --> 36:20.950
You do not get to use me.

36:20.985 --> 36:23.453
Violet, I'm done with people dying.

36:23.487 --> 36:26.456
Enough! Get out!

36:26.490 --> 36:28.458
[Whooshing]

36:28.492 --> 36:31.260
[Coughing]

36:32.496 --> 36:35.264
[Coughing]

36:35.299 --> 36:37.367
[Panting]

36:41.605 --> 36:44.507
Violet's gone. [Sighs]

36:44.541 --> 36:48.277
She said what she wanted you to know.

36:48.312 --> 36:50.980
Her spirit moved on.

36:51.015 --> 36:54.183
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

36:54.218 --> 36:56.486
You okay?

36:56.520 --> 36:57.987
No.

36:58.022 --> 37:01.958
You promised me peace.

37:01.992 --> 37:04.160
I know. I'm sorry.

37:04.194 --> 37:06.162
So am I.

37:06.196 --> 37:07.497
<i>♪</i>

37:07.531 --> 37:10.633
[Structure Rumbling]

37:11.535 --> 37:14.637
[Glass Shattering]

37:20.210 --> 37:23.312
<i>♪</i>

37:29.386 --> 37:32.355
<i>[Solemn Music]</i>

37:32.389 --> 37:37.860
<i>♪</i>

37:37.895 --> 37:39.962
Thank you. Can I just say...

37:39.997 --> 37:43.533
What were you thinking?

37:43.567 --> 37:45.234
Can we do this in the evening?

37:45.269 --> 37:48.204
Fiji was kidnapped,
and you didn't tell me?

37:48.238 --> 37:50.173
Bobo made the call. Talk to him.

37:50.207 --> 37:52.208
I'm getting my stake, and
I'm gonna stab the sh...

37:52.242 --> 37:54.310
You were worried about me.

37:57.114 --> 37:59.082
I love you, too.

37:59.116 --> 38:04.987
<i>♪</i>

38:05.022 --> 38:09.292
I need you to stop almost dying.

38:11.028 --> 38:13.496
I'm already dead.

38:13.530 --> 38:18.101
<i>♪</i>

38:18.135 --> 38:19.569
[Door Creaks Open]

38:24.241 --> 38:27.310
[Footsteps Approaching]

38:31.949 --> 38:34.217
How are you?

38:34.251 --> 38:36.052
Better.

38:39.490 --> 38:43.259
I didn't know they were
gonna bomb that church.

38:43.293 --> 38:45.361
I was 17,

38:45.395 --> 38:48.364
and my dad... he asked
me to come with him.

38:48.398 --> 38:51.601
<i>♪</i>

38:51.635 --> 38:55.204
Said he was gonna teach me something.

38:55.239 --> 38:56.706
I stayed in the car,

38:56.740 --> 39:00.109
and by the time I figured
out what was happening,

39:00.144 --> 39:01.944
it was too late.

39:01.979 --> 39:04.247
<i>♪</i>

39:04.281 --> 39:06.349
But I saw who they were.

39:08.018 --> 39:10.553
That night when they
were celebrating, I left.

39:10.587 --> 39:13.322
Haven't seen my family since.

39:13.357 --> 39:16.425
Guess I figured they were...

39:16.460 --> 39:18.394
dead.

39:18.428 --> 39:19.962
You never talked about them.

39:19.997 --> 39:22.632
This isn't about them.

39:22.666 --> 39:27.170
<i>♪</i>

39:27.204 --> 39:29.305
It's about you and me.

39:30.808 --> 39:33.342
I should've told you the truth.

39:33.377 --> 39:36.345
I was ashamed.

39:36.380 --> 39:39.081
Afraid of how you'd react.

39:39.116 --> 39:41.684
I thought I knew you.

39:41.718 --> 39:43.686
<i>♪</i>

39:43.720 --> 39:46.255
Like, really, deeply knew you.

39:46.290 --> 39:48.758
Sad thing is, you do.

39:48.792 --> 39:51.994
<i>♪</i>

39:52.029 --> 39:56.098
But I understand why
you think otherwise.

39:56.133 --> 39:58.768
I need time.

39:58.802 --> 40:06.075
<i>♪</i>

40:07.177 --> 40:08.511
I'm here for you, Fiij.

40:08.545 --> 40:10.313
[Julien Baker'S "Funeral Pyre"]

40:10.347 --> 40:17.286
<i>♪ Wake up with the
same pain every night ♪</i>

40:17.321 --> 40:19.322
<i>♪ Digging a hatchet... ♪</i>

40:19.356 --> 40:20.790
You made it out alive.

40:20.824 --> 40:22.358
Did he?

40:22.392 --> 40:24.360
<i>♪</i>

40:24.394 --> 40:26.829
Long story.

40:26.864 --> 40:30.299
I wasn't sure I'd see you again after...

40:30.334 --> 40:33.469
Your dead ex-fiancé fiasco?

40:33.503 --> 40:35.338
Look, if it's a deal breaker, I...

40:35.372 --> 40:37.340
It isn't.

40:37.374 --> 40:40.042
<i>♪</i>

40:40.077 --> 40:41.811
I'm impressed. You did
everything you could

40:41.845 --> 40:44.814
to make it right.

40:44.848 --> 40:46.549
You tried.

40:46.583 --> 40:48.417
<i>♪</i>

40:48.452 --> 40:51.420
I'm sorry about what
happened with your grandma.

40:51.455 --> 40:53.322
That really sucks.

40:53.357 --> 40:55.458
Yeah. It did.

40:57.094 --> 41:04.066
<i>♪</i>

41:04.101 --> 41:07.270
Can you stay a while?

41:07.304 --> 41:09.739
How about I stay the night?

41:11.208 --> 41:13.743
What are you gonna tell your dad?

41:13.777 --> 41:15.711
I already told him the truth:

41:15.746 --> 41:19.181
that I'm an adult, and he
can't tell me how to live,

41:19.216 --> 41:23.419
and you and I are a thing.

41:23.453 --> 41:26.555
I mean, if you're still
planning on staying.

41:26.590 --> 41:30.426
Now I am.

41:30.460 --> 41:35.898
<i>♪ And I would've loved you... ♪</i>

41:35.933 --> 41:39.702
So, I'm not running anymore.

41:39.736 --> 41:42.772
You're not hiding from your dad.

41:42.806 --> 41:44.874
This gonna get boring?

41:44.908 --> 41:46.876
Let's find out.

41:46.910 --> 41:48.878
[Both Chuckle Softly]

41:48.912 --> 41:51.514
<i>♪</i>

41:58.588 --> 42:01.691
[Cracking]

42:05.329 --> 42:06.462
[Critter Hisses]

42:06.496 --> 42:09.465
<i>[Dark Music]</i>

42:09.499 --> 42:12.635
<i>♪</i>

42:12.669 --> 42:14.770
